Patch Set 6: Code-Review-2

I think we can't just remove this code like this. If there are deployments using glance-search, this commit will break them entirely. Can we please deprecate this service and delete it in M? 

It's to be very well document it that project Searchlight is where people need to go now and that in M they won't have this code anymore.

Patch Set 6:

Flavio,

I do not agree with that. 1) The API is EXPERIMENTAL no warranties there 2) The API moved to different project so endpoint change should work as migration plan (and still as experimental there's no guarantee that it would be backwards compatible)

I don't think we need or should carry this forward for extra cycle.

Patch Set 6:

I guess there are two questions here.

1) Are we allowed to rip out an EXPERIMENTAL API without it first being marked DEPRECATED?

See 'status' here for a description:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/VersionDiscovery

My guess is 'yes'.

2) If we are 'allowed', would we seriously inconvenience anyone if we just went ahead and did it?

My guess is 'no'.

We could think about getting clarification (dev mailing list?) on (1).
Maybe for (2) check on the operator mailing list?

As long as we can confirm we're playing by the rules and make an effort to check we're not seriously inconveniencing anyone I'm definitely in favour of removing the code.
Removing it ensures that anyone who wants to start/continue experimenting is using Searchlight, which is probably preferable at this point.

Patch Set 6:

So, we did have some discussion in the API working group in IRC and on the mailing list on using the "Experimental" keyword prior to using it.  Here's one message from the thread:

http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-March/059013.html

We could put up a short mini migration guide if needed.  Not sure if that should go into searchlight or glance docs, but anybody actually using it would not look for it in searchlight, they'd probably look in glance.  We have a short blurb on the Glance plugin in searchlight docs.

https://github.com/openstack/searchlight/blob/master/doc/source/plugins/glance.rst

Maybe a very short spec should be written and approved in glance specs that simply says searchlight is replacing the catalog index service and point them to it.  That way it would show up in the specs repo.

Patch Set 6: Code-Review+1

Flavio, people may be using this but if they've enabled this they've ideally been made well aware that this is in EXPERIMENTAL status which means that, yes, it can just disappear like this.

I have 0 qualms about announcing this on the -operators mailing list and then doing it if no one speaks up. In fact, if no one else will, I'll send the message myself.
